-- Comet Properties Ghana Seeks to Raise $60 Million in Initial Share Sale
-- Moses Dzawu
-- 2010-06-28T11:33:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-28/comet-properties-ghana-seeks-to-raise-60-million-in-initial-share-sale.html

          
          
             Comet Properties Ltd., a Ghanaian
real-estate development company, plans to raise $60 million in a
share sale and will list on the  West African nation’s  exchange,
said Worldwide Securities Ltd., Comet’s advisor on the listing.  
 “Considering the potential of Comet and the amount of
funds to be raised, substantial foreign investor participation
is expected,” Rexford Adomako-Bonsu, chairman of Worldwide
Securities Ltd., said in an interview in the capital, Accra, on
June 25.  
 The company’s currently trade on the Ghana Stock Exchange’s
over-the-counter market. Comet, which was founded in 2002 and
has built 400 housing units since then, expects approval for the
share sale and listing from the Ghanaian Securities and Exchange
Commission within the next six weeks, Adomako-Bonsu said.  
 The Accra-based company’s net asset value is $300 million,
Adomako-Bonsu said.  
